# Astronomy Research Standards
- Use formal scientific terminology (e.g., Airmass, Zenith, Rayleigh Scattering, Mie Scattering).
- All plots must include axis labels with SI units and clear legends.
- Adhere to AASTeX631 standards for all LaTeX documentation.
- Prioritize academic clarity and conciseness in scientific reporting.